OL,5, A teacher who smashed a window to help 
OL,6, his students to safety during the 1966 
OL,7, Aberfan disaster has died aged 82.     
OL,9,FHowell Williams, from Treharris, was   
OL,10,Fjust 25 when the colliery spoil tip    
OL,11,Fcollapsed, engulfing Pantglas Primary  
OL,12,FSchool on 21 October.                  
OL,14,FThe disaster killed 144 people,        
OL,15,Fincluding 116 children. Four teachers  
OL,16,Fsurvived.                              
OL,18,FMr Williams' son, Jonathan Williams,   
OL,19,F53, said "he was a lovely man" but had 
OL,20,F"struggled" after the disaster.        
